    <li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="dsq-comment-27085">
        <div id="dsq-comment-header-27085" class="dsq-comment-header">
            <cite id="dsq-cite-27085">
                <span id="dsq-author-user-27085">John Slimick</span>
            </cite>
        </div>
        <div id="dsq-comment-body-27085" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-27085" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>WRT to Mark&#8217;s comment: at the end of Wittgenstein&#8217;s<br />
Tractatus TheoPoliticus (well, you know what I mean)<br />
in German is the sentence usually translated into English as:<br />
  &#8220;Of that of which we speak, we should speak    <br />
   clearly;<br />
   if we cannot speak clearly, we should not speak       <br />
   at all.&#8221;</p>
<p>This was part of the original ALGOL definition. I haven&#8217;t seen a similar quote on any definition since.</p>
<p>john slimick<br />
university of pittsburgh at bradford</p>
